    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that's a bit vague lol. i'm seeing a lot of reports saying that the higher benefit amounts are exactly why we're seeing fewer people looking for jobs. can you look into the data that specifically shows how these benefits act as a disincentive? i want to see the link between the subsidies and the drop in participation.",
