      "content": "i get the \"complex issue\" thing but it feels like you're dodging the point. when you look at the actual economic theory, doesn't the basic math show that if you give people enough money to survive without a job, they're naturally going to work less? isn't it pretty much an established fact that these programs create a work disincentive?",
